          "heading": "What is a Transformer?",
          "support_status": "inferred_from_slides",
          "text": "A Transformer is a type of language model, often referred to as a Transformer Language Model (LM) or Generative Pretrained Transformer (GPT) in the context of machine learning. The language model component of a Transformer LM functions similarly to an RNN-LM. A key building block for Transformer language models is attention. Each layer within a Transformer LM is comprised of several sublayers, which include attention, a feed-forward neural network, layer normalization, and residual connections."
        }
